                  </g>
                </g>
              </svg>
            </div>
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div itemscope="" itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" class="faq--answer">
        <div itemprop="text">
          
            <p>The term <a href="https://www.psychologytoday.com/us/blog/worrier-warrior/201511/the-twice-exceptional-adult">twice-exceptional,</a> often abbreviated as 2e, refers to intellectually <a href="https://www.psychologytoday.com/us/basics/intelligence" title="Psychology Today looks at gifted" class="basics-link" hreflang="en-US">gifted</a> children who have some form of disability. These children are considered exceptional because of their intellectual gifts and because of their special needs. These so-called disabilities often include diagnoses on the autism spectrum and <a href="https://www.psychologytoday.com/us/basics/adhd" title="Psychology Today looks at ADHD" class="basics-link" hreflang="en-US">ADHD</a>. Parents are increasingly seeking help for their children in this realm, as are many adults themselves.</p>
      
        </div>
      </div>
      </div>

            </div>
                        </div>

    
        
  </div>
</div>
      </div>


      </div>
    
    
    
                
          <div class="views-element-container"><div class="js-view-dom-id-c9cfa08592e8aa84f6b164d17fb776c15e539b5fc83df661536d50dac9b03f95">
  
  
  

  
  
  

  <section class="basics--essential-reads">

    <div class="h2 page-section-header">Essential Reads</div>
  
          <div class="teaser--card-inset-details--row">
    

<article class="teaser--card-inset-details blog_entry--teaser--card-inset-details" data-nid="5018027">

      <div class="card-inset-details__image">
      
              <a href="/us/blog/promoting-empathy-with-your-teen/202403/reducing-meltdowns-in-children-with-autism-spectrum"><img loading="lazy" src="https://cdn2.psychologytoday.com/assets/styles/manual_crop_3_2_600x400/public/teaser_image/blog_entry/2024-03/AdobeStock_637151593.jpeg.jpg?itok=XwK-r_Lf" width="600" height="400" alt="" title="By Visionarily on AdobeStock" />

</a>

      
    </div>
  
  <div class="card-inset-details__body">

          <div class="card-inset-details__title">
        <a href="/us/blog/promoting-empathy-with-your-teen/202403/reducing-meltdowns-in-children-with-autism-spectrum" title="Reducing Meltdowns in Children With Autism Spectrum"> Reducing Meltdowns in Children With Autism Spectrum </a>
      </div>
    
          <div class="card-inset-details__teaser-text">
        
            Supporting children on the autism spectrum in managing meltdowns is a common challenge for children and their families.
      
      </div>
    
  </div>

</article>


  
    

<article class="teaser--card-inset-details blog_entry--teaser--card-inset-details" data-nid="5015985">

      <div class="card-inset-details__image">
      
              <a href="/us/blog/women-with-autism-spectrum-disorder/202401/autistic-boys-and-men-camouflage-too"><img loading="lazy" src="https://cdn2.psychologytoday.com/assets/styles/manual_crop_3_2_600x400/public/teaser_image/blog_entry/2024-01/hand-holding-mask-on-a-face-2023-11-27-05-00-51-utc.jpg?itok=fiujdKUl" width="600" height="400" alt="" title="Rawpixel, Envato" />

</a>

      
    </div>
  
  <div class="card-inset-details__body">

          <div class="card-inset-details__title">
        <a href="/us/blog/women-with-autism-spectrum-disorder/202401/autistic-boys-and-men-camouflage-too" title="Autistic Boys and Men Camouflage, Too"> Autistic Boys and Men Camouflage, Too </a>
      </div>
    
          <div class="card-inset-details__teaser-text">
        
            Camouflaging and masking behaviors in autistic women and girls have received considerable attention in recent years, but camouflaging is not limited to one gender.
      
      </div>
    
  </div>

</article>      </div>
    


  
          <div class="teaser--card-inset-details--row">
    

<article class="teaser--card-inset-details blog_entry--teaser--card-inset-details" data-nid="5011735">

      <div class="card-inset-details__image">
      
              <a href="/us/blog/donor-family-matters/202310/dna-matters-psychological-differences-in-donor-families"><img loading="lazy" src="https://cdn2.psychologytoday.com/assets/styles/manual_crop_3_2_600x400/public/teaser_image/blog_entry/2023-12/Graphic%20DNA%20Brain.jpeg.jpg?itok=GBeVm35z" width="600" height="400" alt="" title="retrorocket@123rf" />

</a>

      
    </div>
  
  <div class="card-inset-details__body">

          <div class="card-inset-details__title">
        <a href="/us/blog/donor-family-matters/202310/dna-matters-psychological-differences-in-donor-families" title="DNA Matters: Psychological Differences in Donor Families"> DNA Matters: Psychological Differences in Donor Families </a>
      </div>
    
          <div class="card-inset-details__teaser-text">
        
            Knowing one&#039;s family medical history and having updated information on the psychological health of unknown genetic relatives is crucial for donor family members.
      
      </div>
    
  </div>

</article>


  
    

<article class="teaser--card-inset-details blog_entry--teaser--card-inset-details" data-nid="5006900">

      <div class="card-inset-details__image">
      
              <a href="/us/blog/brothers-sisters-strangers/202305/a-hidden-cause-of-troubled-family-relationships"><img loading="lazy" src="https://cdn2.psychologytoday.com/assets/styles/manual_crop_3_2_600x400/public/teaser_image/blog_entry/2023-06/shutterstock_1166395354.jpg?itok=m4gpVEPQ" width="600" height="400" alt="" title="Olena Yakobchuk/Shutterstock" />

</a>

      
    </div>
  
  <div class="card-inset-details__body">

          <div class="card-inset-details__title">
        <a href="/us/blog/brothers-sisters-strangers/202305/a-hidden-cause-of-troubled-family-relationships" title="A Hidden Cause of Some Difficult Family Relationships"> A Hidden Cause of Some Difficult Family Relationships </a>
      </div>
    
          <div class="card-inset-details__teaser-text">
        
            Undiagnosed autism limits the emotional connection of adult relationships in the family; it could be a hidden cause of troubled relationships.
      
      </div>
    
  </div>

</article>      </div>
    


